The Telegraph - Calcutta : Business
 Saturday, May 08, 2004  Business Briefs																								 Mumbai, May 7: Hindustan Lever Ltd (HLL) and PepsiCo have formed an alliance to sell and distribute Lipton ready-to-drink tea and tea-based beverages here. The agreement, signed today between HLLs largest selling tea brand, Lipton, and Pepsi, would target a national presence building on the soft-drink majors market leadership in the country, HLL said in a release. The companies are developing and testing a slew of products for launching in the local market, it said.																								 New Delhi, May 7: A solution to the Dabhol power project appears to be in sight with IDBI-led financial institutions eager to thrash out their disputes with the offshore lenders at the forthcoming meet on May 12 in London.																								 New Delhi, May 7: Lufthansa plans to introduce its new Business Class service to the newly-launched New Delhi-Munich route scheduled from June 9.																								 New Delhi, May 7: The G-20 nations, including India and Brazil, today rejected the blended formula for tariff reduction on agriculture proposed by the US and the European Commission, the commerce ministry said.																								 Calcutta, May 7: Tata Iron and Steel Co Ltd (Tisco) has signed a shareholders agreement with Unistretch Limited for exploration of limestone and development of mines in Thailand.
